tions and the use of game theory, advancing the present science of adversarial risk analysis, are discussed. The book further stands up for developing and employing dynamic security risk assessments, for instance based on Bayesian networks, and using OR methods to truly move security forward in the chemical and process industries.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aChemical industryxRisk assessment. 0aChemical industryxSecurity measures. 0aChemical industry. 0aChemical plantsxSafety measures. 0aRisk management. 4aChemieingenieurwesen. 4aChemische Industrie. 4aRisikomanagement. 4aVerfahrenstechnik.1 aArgenti, Francesca, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBajpai, Shailendra, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBaybutt, Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCozzani, Valerio, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGupta, J. P., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaskins, Cecilia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKhakzad, Nima, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKhakzad, Nima, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLanducci, Gabriele, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMoore, David A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPaltrinieri, Nicola, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPasman, Hans J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPasman, Hans, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aReniers, Genserik, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aReniers, Ge